{"workflow_number":378,"workflow_id":"ed-allergic-reaction-documentation","title":"ED allergic reaction documentation","specialty":"Emergency Medicine documentation-only","diagnosis":"ED allergic reaction documentation","research_status":"partial_source_support","research_status_label":"Partial source support","uae_applicability":"Clinical documentation concepts transfer, but UAE allergy referral, pharmacovigilance, formulary and emergency pathways apply.","uae_findings":[{"finding_type":"partial_applicability","evidence_basis":"Structured source status remains partial_exact_source_verified."}],"source_references":[{"source_resolves":true,"source_id":"nice-drug-allergy-cg183-2014","title":"Drug allergy: diagnosis and management — Recommendations","issuing_organisation":"National Institute for Health and Care Excellence","official_url":"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg183/chapter/recommendations","jurisdiction":"United Kingdom; international evidence requiring UAE allergy, emergency, medicine, and referral adaptation","sections":[{"section_id":"nice-cg183-drug-allergy-assessment-patterns","heading":"Recommendation 1.1.1 and Tables 1–3 — assessment, reaction patterns, and timing","locator":"official recommendations lines 39–121","evidence_summary":"Supports documenting history, examination, timing after exposure, erythema, urticaria, angioedema, respiratory or cardiovascular features, macules, papules, fixed eruption, fever, lymphadenopathy, mucosal erosion, vesicles, blistering, detachment, pustules, photosensitivity, and vasculitic features without asserting a diagnosis."},{"section_id":"nice-cg183-structured-reaction-documentation","heading":"Recommendations 1.2.1–1.2.9 — recording and sharing drug-allergy information","locator":"official recommendations lines 159–234","evidence_summary":"Supports structured recording of drug name, reaction signs, symptoms, severity, date and time, indication, number of doses or days before onset, route, status, and specialist-i